Instructions on how to get build it and run in VS
1. Download and install latest version of Qt (with openGL) 
2. Download and unpack latest version of GLEW
3. Open CMake and navigate to distortionizer directory
4. Add path for build directory like /distortionizer/bin
5. Click "Add Entry" and add C_MAKE_PREFIX_PATH and 
add location of Qt OpenGL directory and Glew directory like below
"C:/Qt/Qt5.4.0-gl/5.4/msvc2013_opengl/lib/cmake;C:/glew"
6. Click "Configure" and it will prompt you to fill a few more 
entries
7. For Qt5Widgets_DIR specify like below (adjust for your path) "C:/Qt/Qt5.4.0-gl/5.4/msvc2013_opengl/lib/cmake/Qt5Widgets"
8. For Qt5OpenGL_DIR specify like below (adjust for your path)
"C:/Qt/Qt5.4.0-gl/5.4/msvc2013_opengl/lib/cmake/Qt5OpenGL"
9. For GLEW_DLL specify like below (adjusting for your path)
"C:/glew/bin/Release/Win32/glew32.dll"
This should allow it to successfull "Configure" and generate VS solution.
10. After you open solution, right click on "distortionizer-calibration" in VS in Solution Explorer widget and select "Set as Startup Project" 
11. In menu header, click on Project -> Properties (or Alt+F7) and in "Configuration Properties" -> Debugging set "Environment" to  "PATH=$(PATH);C:\Qt\Qt5.4.0-gl\5.4\msvc2013_opengl\bin"
otherwise it will complain about missing Qt5OpenGL.dll file
